[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'zacharysarah', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2018-10-19 18:29:11+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': '## This is a...

- [x] Feature Request
- [ ] Bug Report

## Problem

Localization guidelines ask localization (l10n) team admins to [open production branches](https://kubernetes.io/docs/contribute/localization/#branching-strategy) directly against k/website, but in order to do that, team admins need repo write permissions for k/website.

## Proposed solution

Create a [team](https://github.com/kubernetes/website/settings/collaboration) for l10n team admins that gives write permissions to k/website.

Team admins to include | L10n project
---|---
@cstoku | Japanese
@gochist | Korean
@markthink | Chinese

**Note**: Open a separate PR to add @markthink to the following teams in `OWNERS_ALIASES`:

- sig-docs-zh-owners
- sig-docs-zh-reviews

### Caution

Team admins must be mindful that with write power comes write responsibility: closely monitor the health of any long-running branches you create, and ensure that PRs opened directly against k/website fix problems instead of creating them.', 'title': 'L10n team admins need write permissions to k/website', 'type': 'issue'}
